    {
      "question": "The decimal expansion of the rational number $\\frac{43}{2^4 \times 5^3}$ will terminate after how many places of decimals?",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "A rational number $p/q$ in its simplest form terminates after $n$ decimal places if $q = 2^a \times 5^b$, where $n = \\max(a, b)$.",
          "Given $q = 2^4 \times 5^3$.",
          "Here $a = 4$ and $b = 3$.",
          "The number of decimal places is $\\max(4, 3) = 4$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\frac{43}{2^4 \\times 5^3} = \\frac{43 \\times 5^1}{2^4 \\times 5^3 \\times 5^1} = \\frac{215}{2^4 \\times 5^4} = \\frac{215}{10^4} = 0.0215 \\\\ \\text{The number of decimal places is } 4."
      },
      "topic": "Real Numbers",
      "subtopic": "Decimal Expansion of Rational Numbers",
      "marks": 1,
      "type": "mcq",
